===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|συνεργία||joint work, assistance, help|tr=sunergia|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} from {{term|συνεργός||working together|tr=sunergos|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} from {{term|σύν||together|tr=sun|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} + {{term|ἔργον||work|tr=ergon|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈsɪnədʒi/}}, {{SAMPA|/"sIn@dZi/}}
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|sĭnʹər-jē}}, {{IPA|/ˈsɪnɚdʒi/}}, {{SAMPA|/"sIn@`dZi/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|synergies}}

# [[behavior|Behavior]] of a [[system]] that cannot be [[predict]]ed by the behavior of its [[part]]s.
# {{medicine}} Combined [[action]]; the combined healthy action of every [[organ]] of a particular system; as, the [[digestive]] synergy.
# {{pharmacology}} An [[interaction]] between [[drug]]s where the effects are stronger than their mere sum.
# Benefits [[result]]ing from [[combine|combining]] two [[different]] [[group]]s, [[people]], [[object]]s or [[process]]es.

====Usage notes====
* {{term||Synergy}} is frequently dismissed as business [[jargon]].

